#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.120"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.120:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.120:0.2"
msgid "12. Lokakāmaguṇavagga"
msgstr "12. The World and the Kinds of Sensual Stimulation"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 120. Sāriputtasaddhivihārikasutta → sāriputta (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.120:0.3"
msgid "120. Sāriputtasaddhivihārikasutta"
msgstr "120. Sāriputta and the Pupil"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.120:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn35.120:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged "
"greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn35.120:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so bhikkhu āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn35.120:1.4"
msgid ""
"“saddhivihāriko, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, a mendicant pupil of mine has rejected the training and "
"returned to a lesser life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.104"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.120:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Evametaṃ, āvuso, hoti indriyesu aguttadvārassa, bhojane amattaññuno, "
"jāgariyaṃ ananuyuttassa."
msgstr ""
"“That’s how it is, reverend, when someone doesn’t guard the sense doors, "
"eats too much, and is not committed to wakefulness."

msgctxt "sn35.120:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘So vatāvuso, bhikkhu indriyesu aguttadvāro bhojane amattaññū jāgariyaṃ "
"ananuyutto yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ santānessatī’ti "
"netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s not possible for such a mendicant to maintain the full and pure "
"spiritual life for the rest of their life."

msgctxt "sn35.120:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘So vatāvuso, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro, bhojane mattaññū, jāgariyaṃ "
"anuyutto yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ santānessatī’ti "
"ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"But it is possible for a mendicant to maintain the full and pure spiritual "
"life for the rest of their life if they guard the sense doors, eat in "
"moderation, and are committed to wakefulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.120:3.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how does someone guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī."
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.9"
msgid ""
"Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "sn35.120:3.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how someone guards the sense doors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.120:4.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhojane mattaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does someone eat in moderation?"

msgctxt "sn35.120:4.2"
msgid "Idhāvuso, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat:"

msgctxt "sn35.120:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya, na madāya, na maṇḍanāya, na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa "
"kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā, brahmacariyānuggahāya. Iti "
"purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me "
"bhavissati, anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

msgctxt "sn35.120:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhojane mattaññū hoti."
msgstr "That’s how someone eats in moderation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.105"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.120:5.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is someone committed to wakefulness?"

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ "
"parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant practices walking and sitting meditation by day, "
"purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.3"
msgid ""
"Rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ "
"parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"In the evening, they continue to practice walking and sitting meditation."

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.4"
msgid ""
"Rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti pāde pādaṃ "
"accādhāya sato sampajāno, uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā."
msgstr ""
"In the middle of the night, they lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right "
"side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on "
"the time of getting up."

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.5"
msgid ""
"Rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"In the last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking "
"and sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, āvuso, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti."
msgstr "That’s how someone is committed to wakefulness."

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.7"
msgid "Tasmātihāvuso, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.8"
msgid ""
"‘indriyesu guttadvārā bhavissāma, bhojane mattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will guard the sense doors, eat in moderation, and be committed to "
"wakefulness.’"

msgctxt "sn35.120:5.9"
msgid "Evañhi vo, āvuso, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.120:5.10"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
